# Documentation (project level)

Complements `inline-documentation.mdc` (line/function level) with file- and project-level expectations.

## README and AGENTS.md

- **`README.md`** — user-facing overview, quick start, layout, progressive learning params, disclaimer. Update when CLI commands, config keys, or artifact paths change.
- **`AGENTS.md`** — durable, non-obvious context for Cursor/Cloud agents: architecture one-liners, cloud gotchas (CCXT 451, synthetic fallback, `.venv` paths, fast smoke commands). Update when agent-relevant behavior changes.

## Module and API docs

- Public modules in `epoch_ai/` should have a module docstring explaining purpose and key entry points.
- Public classes and functions need docstrings describing parameters, returns, and side effects (artifacts written, SQLite rows inserted).
- Config models in `settings.py` use Pydantic `Field(description=...)` for every user-facing knob.

## Cursor rules

- When adding a new cross-cutting concern (new artifact type, new optional integration, new test gate), add or update a focused rule in `.cursor/rules/` rather than bloating `agent.mdc`.
- Keep rule filenames kebab-case (`ml-causality.mdc`, not `ML_Causality.md`).

## Before "done"

- If behavior, CLI surface, config schema, or cloud constraints changed, confirm README and/or AGENTS.md were updated in the same change set (`definition-of-done.mdc`).
- Research/educational disclaimer in README must remain intact for trading-related changes.
